===Anime===
Directed by Manabu Ono and Kenji Seto, an anime adaptation of the series was broadcast from October 3 to December 15, 2015, with a second season following from April 2 through June 18, 2016.

Four pieces of theme music are used for the two seasons: two opening themes and two ending themes. The opening themes, "Brand-new world" and "The Asterisk War", are both performed by [[Shiena Nishizawa]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Asterisk War Anime's TV Ad Streamed|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-09-10/the-asterisk-war-anime-tv-ad-streamed/.92764|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=February 23, 2018|date=September 11, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Asterisk War 2nd Season Anime's Trailer English-Subtitled|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-03-23/the-asterisk-war-2nd-season-anime-trailer-english-subtitled/.100147|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=February 23, 2018|date=March 24, 2016}}</ref> The first ending theme, titled "Waiting for the rain", is performed by [[Maaya Sakamoto]],<ref>{{cite web|title=The Asterisk War Anime's 2nd Promo Video Reveals Cast|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-07-19/the-asterisk-war-anime-2nd-promo-video-reveals-cast/.90640|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=February 23, 2018|date=July 19, 2015}}</ref> while the second ending theme is {{nihongo|"[[Ai no Uta (Words of Love)]]"|愛の詩}} performed by [[Haruka Chisuga]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Haruka Chisuga Performs The Asterisk War 2nd Season's Ending Theme Song|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-02-14/haruka-chisuga-performs-the-asterisk-war-2nd-season-ending-theme-song/.98676|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|accessdate=February 23, 2018|date=February 15, 2016}}</ref>

[[Aniplex of America]] licensed the series for an English-language release in North and South America and simulcasted the series on [[Crunchyroll]]'s streaming services.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-09-22/aniplex-usa-licenses-the-asterisk-war-anime/.93265|title=Aniplex USA Licenses The Asterisk War Anime|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=September 22, 2015|accessdate=September 22, 2015}}</ref> Aniplex released the series on DVD and Blu-ray in four compilations, each containing 6 episodes, from September 20, 2016 to April 25, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Asterisk War Volume 1 Limited Edition Blu-Ray|url=https://www.rightstufanime.com/The-Asterisk-War-Volume-1-Limited-Edition-Blu-ray|publisher=[[Right Stuf, Inc.]]|accessdate=December 20, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Asterisk War Volume 4 Limited Edition Blu-Ray|url=https://www.rightstufanime.com/The-Asterisk-War-Volume-4-Limited-Edition-Blu-ray|publisher=[[Right Stuf, Inc.]]|accessdate=December 20, 2017}}</ref>

